    // The problem condition "every cycle's edge weight sum is even" is equivalent
    // to saying that the graph must be bipartite when considering edge weights modulo 2.
    // Since weights are 0 or 1, we are concerned with parity.
    // If we consider a graph where edge weight w_i is 1 if w_i=1 and 0 if w_i=0,
    // the condition means that for any cycle, the sum of weights (modulo 2) must be 0.
    // This is the fundamental property of a bipartite graph coloring, but applied to parities.

    // We can use a Disjoint Set Union (DSU) structure modified to track relative parity.
    // For each node i, we will maintain:
    // 1. parent[i]: The parent of node i in the DSU tree.
    // 2. parity[i]: The parity of the path distance (sum of weights modulo 2)
    //    from node i to its current parent (parent[i]).

    const parent = Array(n).fill(0).map((_, i) => i);
    // parity[i] stores the parity of the path sum from i to parent[i].
    // 0 means even path sum, 1 means odd path sum.
